{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase uniform tax reliefs, especially for healthcare staff",
        "additional_details": "Uniformed workers at this current time will be laundering uniforms (including PPE) far more frequently (perhaps daily given the risks of transmitting COVID-19). Guidance on the NHS website states that \u201chealthcare workers\u2019 uniforms\u201d are classified as \u201chigh risk items\u201d in spreading infection such as coronavirus and should be laundered regularly (especially at the current time). The Government should increase these reliefs for all key workers, and in particular healthcare workers.",
        "background": "Workers in various industries can claim tax relief if they clean their work uniform or spend their own money repairing or replacing equipment they need to do their job. Tax reliefs range from \u00a360-\u00a31,022 a year, and for healthcare staff range from \u00a380-\u00a3185 a year.",
